Success is something everyone wishes for, but it is hard work, determination, and bravery that will get you there. Ever Eden Facebook http://www.facebook.com/EverEdenOfficial Ever Eden Instagram - EverEden Ever Eden Twitter http://www.twitter.com/EverEden Ever Eden is my fashion jewelry line inspired by the harmony  and beauty of heaven and earth. The symbol of Ever Eden consists of a "mandorla" ; an ancient symbol of two circles coming together and overlapping one another to form an almond shape in the middle. The circles represent heaven and earth.  In the 15th century, a brave peasant girl who was the daughter of a shepherd lived an incredible life where she became a solider and helped lead the French army into victory. She claimed to be a messenger from God and at the age of 16, she cut her hair to disguise herself as a young man and went to see the future French king, Charles VII. She impressed him by revealing  to him messages that only he and God can know. Convinced of her divine mission, he gave her the equipment of a knight, suit of armour custom made for her, and presented a large army to Joan. She battled for France and was the driving force behind many of their victories. At the age of 19, she was captured and was executed later to be declared as a saint.  Music from Secret Garden "Pastorale" Ever After "The Ruins"

item.title: El graffiti que proyecta a López Obrador
item.description:
El graffiti que proyecta a López Obrador
El colectivo neomuralista Neza Arte Nel tiene 12 años creando obras que han traspasado fronteras, debido a su forma de conceptualizar las cosas y dejarlas plasmadas en espacios gigantescos, con un estilo que nunca pasa desapercibido. Debido a eso han pintado en varios lugares de España, como Valencia, Zaragoza y Cartagena, así como en varios museos de México, en los que se incluyen el de Arte Moderno, Carrillo Gil y San Ildefonso. Por eso mismo, Yahoo! invitó a este grupo para que en esta época electoral, imprimiera en una superficie lo que a su sentir como jóvenes y artistas, veían en todo este proceso y sus personajes. Neza Arte Nel aceptó el reto y en esta ocasión hizo un mural de López Obrador y su ideología de República Amorosa. Después de seis horas de trabajo este es el resultado que Ozcar Rivera (así con 'z'), Martín Cuaya, Alejandro Medina y Virginia lograron, apoyados por rodillos, pinturas, muchos botes de spray, ingenio y mucho, mucho talento. Míralo desde que era una pared blanca hasta el trabajo final.
